org.glassfish.tyrus.websockets

Class WebSocketEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.glassfish.tyrus.websockets.WebSocketEngine

  • public class WebSocketEngine
extends Object
    WebSockets engine implementation (singleton), which handles WebSocketApplications registration, responsible for client and server handshake validation.
    Author:
    Alexey Stashok
    See Also:
    WebSocket, WebSocketApplication

      • upgrade

        public boolean upgrade(Connection connection,
              WebSocketRequest request)
                throws IOException
        Evaluate whether connection/request is suitable for upgrade and perform it.
        Parameters:
        connection - connection.
        request - request.
        Returns:
        true if upgrade is performed, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurred during the upgrade.

      • upgrade

        public boolean upgrade(Connection connection,
              WebSocketRequest request,
              WebSocketEngine.WebSocketHolderListener webSocketHolderListener)
                throws HandshakeException
        Evaluate whether connection/request is suitable for upgrade and perform it.
        Parameters:
        connection - connection.
        request - request.
        webSocketHolderListener - called when upgrade is going to be performed. Additinally, leaves WebSocket.onConnect() call responsibility to WebSocketEngine.WebSocketHolderListener instance.
        Returns:
        true if upgrade is performed, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        HandshakeException - if an error occurred during the upgrade.

      • register

        public void register(WebSocketApplication app)
              throws DeploymentException
        Registers the specified WebSocketApplication with the WebSocketEngine.
        Parameters:
        app - the WebSocketApplication to register.
        Throws:
        DeploymentException - when added applications responds to same path as some already registered application.
